The paper deals with a distributed algorithm for achieving a common least squares solution of a group of linear equations in a multi-agent network. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories such as systems and control (cs.SY), multi-agent systems (cs.MA), distributed computing (cs.DC), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and machine learning (cs.LG).
